title: Software Engineer, Google Cloud
description: Design, develop, test, deploy, maintain and enhance software solutions for Google Cloud products.
requirements: Bachelor's degree in Computer Science or related field
4 years of experience with data structures or algorithms
Experience in one or more of the following: C++, Java, Python, Go, JavaScript, TypeScript, or Rust
responsibilities: Work with a team to develop and maintain software for Google Cloud
Participate in design and code reviews

title: Product Manager, AI/ML
description: Lead the product strategy and roadmap for AI/ML initiatives within Google.
requirements: Bachelor's degree or equivalent practical experience
5 years of experience in product management
Experience with AI/ML technologies and product development
responsibilities: Define and execute product strategy for AI/ML products
Collaborate with engineering, research, and design teams
Drive product launches and go-to-market strategies

title: Data Scientist, Ads
description: Apply statistical methods and machine learning to analyze large datasets and improve Google Ads products.
requirements: Master's or PhD in a quantitative field (e.g., Statistics, Computer Science, Economics)
3 years of experience in data analysis or machine learning
Proficiency in SQL and Python or R
responsibilities: Communicate insights to product and engineering teams

title: UX Designer, Search
description: Design user-friendly and innovative experiences for Google Search products.
requirements: Bachelor's degree in Design, HCI, or related field
4 years of experience in UX design
Proficiency with design tools (e.g., Figma, Sketch, Adobe XD)
responsibilities: Conduct user research and usability testing
Create wireframes, prototypes, and high-fidelity designs
Collaborate with product managers and engineers

title: Software Engineer, Android
description: Develop and maintain core Android platform features and applications.
requirements: Bachelor's degree in Computer Science or related field
3 years of experience in Android development
responsibilities: Design and implement new features for the Android platform
Work with cross-functional teams to deliver high-quality products
